  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of national and international regulations:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Principles\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence procedures\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement AML programs\n- Risk-based screening of customers\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Regular reporting to regulatory authorities\n\n5. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Investigative Mechanisms\n- Inter-agency cooperation\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Advanced digital tracking technologies\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
